<section id="lemmatizing-vs-stemming" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="lemmatizing-vs-stemming">Lemmatizing vs Stemming</h2>
<p>Once you‚Äôve made it this far, should you lemmatize or stem your words? Lemmatization is when you cut the suffix off a word and replace it with the normalized form of the word, while stemming refers to cutting the suffix off completely. A good example of this is if you have the word ‚Äúrunning‚Äù, the stemmed version would be ‚Äúrunn‚Äù while the lemmatized version would be ‚Äúrun‚Äù. You can see that by lemmatizing your words, you convert it into it‚Äôs root word, while stemming could create almost like a second version of the word, which your model might see as a completely separate word. This is why I highly suggest <strong>lemmatizing</strong> your words rather than stemming them.</p>
<p>Python Example:</p>
<div id="74a312ce" class="cell" data-execution_count="8">
